{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, recognising the relationship between language and the performance of AI-based algorithms is crucial for addressing the recurrent issues of bias and suboptimal decisions.Trust in decision-making algorithms depends on users' perceptions of agency and responsibility.",
    "Studies indicate that users are more inclined to trust algorithms that operate autonomously and consistently produce reliable outcomes [10,11].",
    "In contrast, when algorithms are seen as influenced by external factors, such as human biases, their trustworthiness may be questioned [10].",
    "Additionally, the fulfillment of responsibilities and accountability by actors involved in developing and deploying decision-making algorithms significantly impacts trust.",
    "When developers and operators meet their obligations and are held accountable for their actions, users tend to have greater trust in the overall integrity and reliability of the algorithms."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Studies indicate that users are more inclined to trust algorithms that operate autonomously and consistently produce reliable outcomes [10,11].",
    "In contrast, when algorithms are seen as influenced by external factors, such as human biases, their trustworthiness may be questioned [10]."
  ]
}